cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the design and implementation of a LoRa network server architecture for LPWA networks. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the proposed architecture is modularized and based on microservice principles, which involves distributed computing. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper mentions the use of a messaging system based on streaming data, which may involve data structures and algorithms for efficient processing and delivery. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a potential category as the paper discusses the management and scheduling of resources in the LoRa network server, which may involve control systems. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also possible as the paper presents the implementation of the X-LoRa architecture and discusses its technical features and functionality.
